		<td><b>List of Super Mario Bros. glitches</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was testing out my emulator by playing levels of Super Mario Bros when a trampoline disappeared on me.  When I jumped on the spot where the trampoline should have appeared, Mario got stuck.  <br /><br />After spending an hour trying to reproduce the issue so I could debug what was wrong, I discovered that it was a very real glitch in the game.  Hence, I decided to post the link below to warn future developers of the surprisingly large number of glitches in a classic game that I thought I knew well: <br /><br /><a href="http://www.mariowiki.com/List_of_Super_Mario_Bros._glitches" class="postlink">http://www.mariowiki.com/List_of_Super_Mario_Bros._glitches</a>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


